!!! Strict
%html{:xmlns => "http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"}
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=utf-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    %title jsTree v.1.0 - cookies documentation
    %script{:src => "../js/jquery.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../js/jquery.cookie.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../js/jquery.hotkeys.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../js/jquery.jstree.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %link{:href => "syntax/!style.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
    %link{:href => "!style.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
    %script{:src => "syntax/!script.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
  %body
    #container
      %h1 jsTree v.1.0 - cookies plugin
      %h2 Description
      #description
        %p
          The
          %code cookies
          enables jstree to save the state of the tree across sessions. What this does is save the opened and selected nodes in a cookie, and reopen &amp; reselect them the next time the user loads the tree. Depends on the
          %a{:href => "http://plugins.jquery.com/project/cookie"} jQuery.cookie
          plugin.
      %h2#configuration Configuration
      .panel.configuration
        %h3 save_opened
        %p.meta
          A string (or
          = succeed ")." do
            %code false
          Default is
          = succeed "." do
            %code "jstree_open"
        %p
          The name of the cookie to save opened nodes in. If set to
          %code false
          \- opened nodes won't be saved.
        %h3 save_selected
        %p.meta
          A string (or
          = succeed ")." do
            %code false
          Default is
          = succeed "." do
            %code "jstree_select"
        %p
          The name of the cookie to save selected nodes in. If set to
          %code false
          \- selected nodes won't be saved.
        %h3 auto_save
        %p.meta
          A Boolean. Default is
          = succeed "." do
            %code true
        %p
          If set to
          %code true
          jstree will automatically update the cookies every time a change in the state occurs.
        %h3 cookie_options
        %p.meta
          An object. Default is
          = succeed "." do
            %code {}
        %p
          The options accepted by the
          %a{:href => "http://plugins.jquery.com/project/cookie"} jQuery.cookie
          plugin.
      %h2#demos Demos
      .panel
        %p
          Check your data plugin documentation (
          %a{:href => "html_data.html"}> html_data
          ,
          = succeed "," do
            %a{:href => "xml_data.html"} xml_data
          = succeed ")" do
            %a{:href => "json_data.html"} json_data
          or take a close look at these examples for information on how to specify multilanguage nodes.
        %h3 Using the cookies plugin
        %p
          Go ahead and make changes to the tree and then
          = succeed "." do
            %a{:href => "javascript:document.location.reload();"} refresh this page
        #demo1.demo
          %ul
            %li#phtml_1
              %a{:href => "#"} Root node 1
              %ul
                %li#phtml_2
                  %a{:href => "#"} Child node 1
                %li#phtml_3
                  %a{:href => "#"} Child node 2
            %li#phtml_4
              %a{:href => "#"} Root node 2
        %script.source{:type => "text/javascript"}
          $(function () {
          $("#demo1").jstree({
          "plugins" : [ "themes", "html_data", "ui", "cookies" ]
          });
          });
      %h2#api API
      .panel.api
        %h3#save_cookie .save_cookie ( event )
        %p Save the current state.
        %ul.arguments
          %li
            %code.tp string
            %strong event
            %p
              Used internally with the
              %code auto_save
              option. Do not set this manually.
